description: Romano-British agricultural site, with a circular limestone founded building with a central square feature. The building is not well dated but the 2nd CE is suggested based on other finds, the building has been interpreted as a shrine based on minimal evidence.
bibliography: Hall, and Nickerson. “Circular Roman Building at Bozeat, Northamptonshire, 1964.” Bedfordshire Archaeology 5 (1970).
Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Bozeat (Northamptonshire).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
Meadows. “Three Roman Sites in Northamptonshire: Excavations by E. Greenfield at Bozeat, Higham Ferrers, and Great Oakley between 1961 and 1966.” Northamptonshire Archaeology 24 (1992).
